<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 MODEL - DETROIT DIESEL SERIES 60 ENGINE - TROUBLESHOOTING -
        PARK BRAKE (IDLE TIMER) SWITCH (328) - DETROIT DIESEL
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>PARK BRAKE (IDLE TIMER) SWITCH (328) - DETROIT DIESEL</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Inspect circuits and connectors as outlined in
                <hotlnk document="s08270_166.xml" xrefid="x0827801">Before Troubleshooting.</hotlnk>
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing Park Brake Switch (328) and Circuits - Detroit Diesel</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Vehicle air system must be fully charged for this test.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <table id="t0827814" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing Park Brake Switch (328) and Circuits - Detroit Diesel</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.80in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.97in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.69in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.82in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.34in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7" rotate="0">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Remove connector (328) from the park brake switch. With park brake applied,
                                    measure resistance across switch terminals.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Switch (328), across terminals.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>&#60; 5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace the (328) switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>With park brake applied, measure resistance to ground at both switch terminals.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Switch (328), term. to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>> 100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace the switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Release park brake and measure resistance between switch terminals.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Switch (328), across term.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>> 100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Replace the switch.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At connector (328) measure resistance from 97-GE to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(328), 97-GE to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>&#60; 5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 97-GE, 97-GA, 97-G or 11-G to negative
                                    battery terminal, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Remove connector (341) from ECM. At connector (341) measure resistance from H2
                                    (circuit 97AV) to ground.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(341), H2 to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>> 100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate short to ground in circuit 97AV between connectors (341) and (328), then
                                    repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>At connector (341) terminal H2 (circuit 97AV) , measure voltage to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(341), H2 to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>&#60; 1 volt.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate short to unwanted voltage source in circuit 97AV, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>7.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Connect (328) to park brake switch, and apply park brake. At connector (341)
                                    measure resistance to ground at terminal H2 (circuit 97AV).
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>(341), H2 to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>&#60; 5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Park brake (idle timer) switch (328) and circuits check good.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry rotate="0">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 97AV between connectors (341) and (328),
                                    then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
